      <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">
        How much does it cost to replace a roof in Tampa?
        <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <div class="faq-answer-inner">A typical roof replacement in Tampa Bay costs between $8,000 and $25,000 for a single-family home in 2026. Asphalt shingles are the most affordable option ($8,000–$16,000), followed by flat/TPO ($12,000–$25,000), metal standing seam ($15,000–$30,000), and tile ($18,000–$35,000). These ranges are for a typical 2,000 sq ft home and include tear-off, materials, labor, permits, and cleanup. Your actual cost depends on roof size, pitch, material, deck condition, and complexity. Call <a href="tel:8135957663" class="call-tracking-number" style="color:#3B9FD9;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600">(813) 595-7663</a> for a free, personalized estimate.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">
        Is a new roof tax deductible in Florida?
        <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <div class="faq-answer-inner">A new roof on your primary residence is generally not tax deductible as a standard home improvement expense. However, there are exceptions. If the replacement is part of an insurance claim for storm damage, out-of-pocket costs may qualify as a casualty loss deduction. Additionally, energy-efficient roofing materials — such as metal roofing or cool-roof-rated shingles — may qualify for federal energy tax credits under the Inflation Reduction Act. Always consult a tax professional for advice specific to your situation.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">
        How long does a roof replacement take?
        <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <div class="faq-answer-inner">Most shingle roof replacements in Tampa Bay take 1 to 3 days. Metal roofs typically take 3 to 5 days, and tile roofs may take 5 to 7 days depending on complexity and weather conditions. Larger homes or roofs with significant deck damage may take longer. Happy Roof handles all permits, county inspections, and job-site cleanup so you don't have to coordinate anything. We keep you informed with updates throughout the project.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <button class="faq-btn" aria-expanded="false" onclick="this.setAttribute('aria-expanded',this.getAttribute('aria-expanded')==='true'?'false':'true');this.nextElementSibling.classList.toggle('open')">
        Does insurance cover roof replacement?
        <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A1A1A" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
      </button>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <div class="faq-answer-inner">Homeowners insurance typically covers roof replacement if the damage was caused by a covered peril — such as a hurricane, hailstorm, tornado, or fallen tree. Normal wear and tear, aging, and lack of maintenance are generally not covered. In Florida, insurance companies may also deny claims if your roof is over a certain age (often 15–20 years). Happy Roof works with all major insurance carriers and can assist with documentation, adjuster meetings, and the claims process. Call <a href="tel:8135957663" class="call-tracking-number" style="color:#3B9FD9;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600">(813) 595-7663</a> to discuss your situation.</div>
